column34: There was a man in the shelter she was staying in who acted as though he was a fellow migrant but whom she suspects was a coyote. This man offered to cross her and her son, but when she didn't immediately agree he threatened her, saying that if she and her son didn't come with the group of migrants he was going to try to cross, something bad could happen to her son. This man also told Maria that he wanted to speak with her husband about the cost of crossing her and her son, so she gave him her husband's phone number. However, when this man called her husband, it was to extort him. He told the husband that he had Maria and their child and asked for ransom money, even though he had not, in fact, kidnapped Maria or her son. Maria's husband was alarmed at the extortion attempts and threatss so he advised Maria to leave the shelter and go to another state in Mexico. She fled to Puebla and was a result missed a hearing and therefore she has an in absentia removal order from January 2020.
